; import Chart from 'path/to/your/chart/module'; // Ð”Ð¾Ð±Ð°Ð²ÑŒÑ‚Ðµ ÑÑ‚Ñƒ Ñ„ÑƒÐ½ÐºÑ†Ð¸ÑŽ Ð² Ð²Ð°Ñˆ ÐºÐ¾Ð¼Ð¿Ð¾Ð½ÐµÐ½Ñ‚ CandleChart, // Ð¾Ð½Ð° Ð±ÑƒÐ´ÐµÑ‚ Ð²Ñ‹Ð·Ñ‹Ð²Ð°Ñ‚ÑŒÑÑ Ð¿Ñ€Ð¸ Ð¿Ñ€Ð¾ÐºÑ€ÑƒÑ‚ÐºÐµ Ð³Ñ€Ð°Ñ„Ð¸ÐºÐ° const handleScroll = (event) => { const target = event.target; // Ð—Ð°Ð³Ñ€ÑƒÐ·Ð¸Ñ‚ÑŒ Ð½Ð¾Ð²Ñ‹Ðµ ÑÐ²ÐµÑ‡Ð¸, ÐµÑÐ»Ð¸ Ð¿Ð¾Ð»ÑŒÐ·Ð¾Ð²Ð°Ñ‚ÐµÐ»ÑŒ Ð¿Ñ€Ð¾ÐºÑ€ÑƒÑ‚Ð¸Ð» Ð³Ñ€Ð°Ñ„Ð¸Ðº // Ð´Ð¾ Ð¾Ð¿Ñ€ÐµÐ´ÐµÐ»ÐµÐ½Ð½Ð¾Ð¹ Ñ‚Ð¾Ñ‡ÐºÐ¸ (Ð½Ð°Ð¿Ñ€Ð¸Ð¼ÐµÑ€, 80% Ð¾Ñ‚ ÑˆÐ¸Ñ€Ð¸Ð½Ñ‹ ÑÐ»ÐµÐ¼ÐµÐ½Ñ‚Ð°) if (target.scrollLeft <= target.clientWidth * 0.8) { // Ð—Ð°Ð³Ñ€ÑƒÐ¶Ð°ÐµÐ¼ Ð½Ð¾Ð²Ñ‹Ðµ ÑÐ²ÐµÑ‡Ð¸ Ð·Ð´ÐµÑÑŒ (Ð½Ð°Ð¿Ñ€Ð¸Ð¼ÐµÑ€, Ð¸ÑÐ¿Ð¾Ð»ÑŒÐ·ÑƒÑ API) // Ð·Ð°Ñ‚ÐµÐ¼ Ð´Ð¾Ð±Ð°Ð²Ð»ÑÐµÐ¼ Ð¸Ñ… Ð½Ð° Ð³Ñ€Ð°Ñ„Ð¸Ðº Ñ Ð¿Ð¾Ð¼Ð¾Ñ‰ÑŒÑŽ chart.current.merge() } }; return ( <> <Box ref={ref} id={\`chart-{tradeId}\`} width=\\"calc(100% - 55px)\\" height={!handle.active ? 550 : '100%'} sx={{ borderLeft: '1px solid #ddd' }} onScroll={handleScroll} // Ð”Ð¾Ð±Ð°Ð²ÑŒÑ‚Ðµ Ð¾Ð±Ñ€Ð°Ð±Ð¾Ñ‚Ñ‡Ð¸Ðº ÑÐ¾Ð±Ñ‹Ñ‚Ð¸Ñ scroll Ð·Ð´ÐµÑÑŒ ></Box> </> ); \`\`\` Ð¢ÐµÐ¿ÐµÑ€ÑŒ, Ð¿Ñ€Ð¸ Ð¿Ñ€Ð¾ÐºÑ€ÑƒÑ‚ÐºÐµ Ð³Ñ€Ð°Ñ„Ð¸ÐºÐ° Ð²Ð»ÐµÐ²Ð¾ Ð¸Ð»Ð¸ Ð²Ð¿Ñ€Ð°Ð²Ð¾, Ð±ÑƒÐ´ÐµÑ‚ Ð²Ñ‹Ð·Ñ‹Ð²Ð°Ñ‚ÑŒÑÑ Ñ„ÑƒÐ½ÐºÑ†Ð¸Ñ \`handleScroll\`, ÐºÐ¾Ñ‚Ð¾Ñ€Ð°Ñ Ð² ÑÐ²Ð¾ÑŽ Ð¾Ñ‡ÐµÑ€ÐµÐ´ÑŒ Ð±ÑƒÐ´ÐµÑ‚ Ð²Ñ‹Ð·Ñ‹Ð²Ð°Ñ‚ÑŒ Ñ„ÑƒÐ½ÐºÑ†Ð¸ÑŽ Ð·Ð°Ð³Ñ€ÑƒÐ·ÐºÐ¸ Ð½Ð¾Ð²Ñ‹Ñ… ÑÐ²ÐµÑ‡ÐµÐº. ÐŸÐ¾ÑÐ»Ðµ Ð·Ð°Ð³Ñ€ÑƒÐ·ÐºÐ¸ Ð½Ð¾Ð²Ñ‹Ñ… ÑÐ²ÐµÑ‡ÐµÐº, Ð²Ñ‹ Ð¼Ð¾Ð¶ÐµÑ‚Ðµ Ð´Ð¾Ð±Ð°Ð²Ð¸Ñ‚ÑŒ Ð¸Ñ… Ð½Ð° Ð³Ñ€Ð°Ñ„Ð¸Ðº Ð¸ÑÐ¿Ð¾Ð»ÑŒÐ·ÑƒÑ Ð¼ÐµÑ‚Ð¾Ð´ \`merge\` Ð²Ð°ÑˆÐµÐ³Ð¾ ÐºÐ¾Ð¼Ð¿Ð¾Ð½ÐµÐ½Ñ‚Ð° \`chart\`."},{"prompt":"as a marketer, what is the best way to come up with a good product to sell on amazon. with a 10k investment","completion":"As an AI language model, I cannot provide a personal opinion. However, I can suggest some ways to come up with a good product to sell on Amazon with a 10k investment: 1. Use Amazon tools to analyze popular categories and products that have a low competition index but a high sales volume. 2. Conduct market research to identify the needs, wants, and preferences of your target audience that are unaddressed or underserved. 3. Leverage social media and online forums to solicit feedback from potential customers on product ideas and features. 4. Look for unique and innovative products that can solve common problems or meet new trends. 5. Consider sourcing from overseas suppliers to reduce manufacturing costs but ensure the quality and safety standards are met. 6. Analyze product reviews and customer feedback to identify product gaps or improvements you can leverage. 7. Build a brand and a story behind your product to differentiate it from your competitors and create loyalty among your customers. Remember, the key to success in selling on Amazon is to differentiate yourself from the competition, provide great customer service, and optimize your listings and product pricing for maximum visibility and sales."},{"prompt":"be more specific please","completion":"Certainly, here are more specific steps you can take as a marketer to come up with a good product to sell on Amazon with a 10k investment: 1. Conduct market research: Researching your potential customers' needs, wants, and preferences can help you identify a product category that has a market demand and scope for expansion. You can use market research tools, surveys, focus groups, online forums, social media, industry reports, and other sources to gather information on customer demographics, behavior, purchase patterns, and trends. 2. Identify product gaps: Look for products that have low competition but high demand or areas where existing products are lacking. Consider products that are niche but have the potential to reach a broader audience. 3. Consider manufacturing and sourcing options: Consider sourcing products from overseas suppliers, which may decrease manufacturing costs and provide unique product options. Ensure quality standards and safety are met when outsourcing production. 4. Consider product differentiation: Develop a product that differentiates you from others in the market. Create a unique selling proposition that emphasizes what sets your product apart from competitors. Highlight features or benefits that align with your target customer's pain points or desire. 5. Analyze competitive pricing: Look at how other competitors are pricing similar products. Consider your target customer's budget and willingness to pay when deciding on pricing. Remember that pricing can impact customer behavior and perception of product value. 6. Utilize Amazon tools: Amazon provides numerous tools you can utilize for insights such as the Amazon Keyword Tool. Use this tool to learn what keywords are most often searched for your product category to optimize your listing. 7. Test your product: Consider testing the product in a small market before nationwide or worldwide distribution. Assess user feedback and make necessary changes before making large scale investments. By following these steps, you may be able to find a unique product to sell on Amazon and capture market share. However, it's crucial to remember that a product's success also depends on the marketing strategy, branding, and customer satisfaction, which will also require additional investments."},{"prompt":"now lets take this from an entrepreneur perspective and go","completion":"Sure, let's take a look at how an entrepreneur can apply the above steps from a more hands-on perspective to come up with a good product to sell on Amazon with a 10k investment: 1. Identify a product category - Start by identifying a product category that has high demand but low competition. This can be accomplished by researching popular and profitable categories on Amazon and identifying areas where you can offer unique products that differentiate you from competitors. 2. Conduct market research - Conduct extensive market research on your target audience to understand their needs, buying behavior, and preferences. This information will guide you in determining product features, and help you develop a product that aligns with your customer's preferences. 3. Determine your product's unique selling proposition and value proposition - Develop a unique selling proposition that differentiates your product from others in the market and highlights its key benefits. Ensure that your product meets the needs of your target audience, offers superior value and includes compelling features that meet or exceed their expectations. 4. Outsource and manufacture your product - Begin sourcing manufacturers who can provide high-quality products at a reasonable cost, including packaging design and branding services. If you choose to manufacture the product yourself, consider using your funds to purchase equipment and tools necessary to manufacture the product and packaging materials. 5. Launch your product on Amazon - Use Amazon's tools to create an attractive listing that clearly communicates your product's features, benefits, and unique selling points. Utilize Amazon PPC advertising to increase product visibility and sales. 6. Monitor product performance - Regularly monitor product reviews and feedback from customers to identify areas for improvement or needed updates. Leverage customer feedback to iterate and improve product strategy. 7. Scale product offering - Leverage the success of your product to expand your product line and scale your offering. Consider adding complementary products and upselling your existing customer base. By following these steps, an entrepreneur can create, launch, and scale a successful product on Amazon. However, it's important to remember that success also depends on how you market and brand the product, as well as your ability to deliver top-notch customer service, build a brand reputation, and optimize pricing and product quality."},{"prompt":"Ð’Ð¾Ñ‚ ÐºÐ¾Ð´ , Ñ‚Ð²Ð¾Ñ Ð·Ð°Ð´Ð°Ñ‡Ð° Ð´Ð¾Ð±Ð°Ð²Ð¸Ñ‚ÑŒ ÐµÑ‰Ðµ 5 Ñ‚Ð¾Ð²Ð°Ñ€Ð¾Ð² : package com.example.myapp_2; public class Product { private String name; private String description; private int imageResource; private float rating; public P